.TH GLOSSARY-SYNC 1 "2026-06-01" "1.0.1" "Zensical Documentation Skills"
.SH NAME
glossary-sync \- maintain and synchronize abbreviations.md with glossary.md
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B glossary-sync
.I command
.RB [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B glossary-sync
is a skill that synchronizes
.I includes/abbreviations.md
(MkDocs abbreviation definitions) with
.I docs/resources/glossary.md
(the resource center glossary) for the zensical-zh-tw documentation project.
.PP
It converts abbreviation entries into SEO-optimized H3 heading format with
concise definitions, English annotations (for acronyms only), and cross-reference
links. It can also clean up abbreviations.md and audit inconsistencies between
the two files.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B sync
Full sync. Parses all entries from abbreviations.md, converts them to H3
glossary format, categorizes into proper sections, adds cross-reference
links, and cleans up English-only plan entries from abbreviations.md.
.TP
.B format
Reformat only. Converts existing glossary.md content to H3 headings without
pulling in new terms from abbreviations.md. Useful for upgrading the format
of an already-complete glossary.
.TP
.B cleanup
Clean abbreviations.md. Removes English-only subscription plan entries
(Regular Plans, PLUS Plans, Professional Plan, etc.) from
abbreviations.md while preserving all other entries.
.TP
.B check
Audit and compare. Reports entries missing from glossary.md, entries
missing from abbreviations.md, and definition differences between the
two files. Read-only; does not modify any files.
.TP
.BI add " term"
Add a new term to both files. Creates an abbreviation entry in
abbreviations.md and a formatted H3 entry in the correct glossary
section. If the term does not fit any existing section, you will
be prompted to specify the section.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Preview all changes without modifying any files.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Show detailed progress for each entry being processed.
.TP
.BI \-\-source " path"
Path to the abbreviations file.
Default: includes/abbreviations.md
.TP
.BI \-\-target " path"
Path to the glossary file.
Default: docs/resources/glossary.md
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
glossary-sync sync
Perform a full sync of abbreviations to glossary.
.TP
glossary-sync sync \-\-dry\-run
Preview what changes a full sync would make.
.TP
glossary-sync format \-\-target docs/resources/glossary.md
Reformat the existing glossary without adding new terms.
.TP
glossary-sync cleanup \-\-source includes/abbreviations.md
Remove English-only plan entries from abbreviations.md.
.TP
glossary-sync check
Compare both files and report inconsistencies.
.TP
glossary-sync add "電子發票" \-\-verbose
Add a new term with detailed progress output.
.SH GLOSSARY FORMAT
Every glossary entry uses H3 headings (never definition lists):
.PP
English acronyms:
.IP
.B "### SKU"
.B "**Stock Keeping Unit（存貨單位）**，用於識別商品的唯一代碼或編號。"
.B "\- **參閱**：[商品管理操作指南](../../resources/商品管理操作指南.md)"
.PP
Pure Chinese terms (no bold annotation):
.IP
.B "### 退貨期限"
.B "商家規定顧客可申請退貨的最長時間範圍，自顧客收到商品起算。"
.B "\- **參閱**：[訂單與物流操作指南](../../resources/訂單物流操作指南.md)"
.SH SECTIONS
.PP
Terms are categorized into one of five H2 sections:
.TP
.B 商品
Product display and basic product information.
.TP
.B 商品結構與規格
Product structure, bundles, variants, and categories.
.TP
.B 訂單、付款與物流
Order management, payment, and logistics.
.TP
.B 行銷與成長
Marketing, analytics, advertising, and growth.
.TP
.B 平台、方案與其他
Platform plans, business models, and miscellaneous.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I includes/abbreviations.md
MkDocs abbreviation definitions (source).
.TP
.I docs/resources/glossary.md
Resource center glossary page (target).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR frontmatterer (1),
.BR permalink\-generator (1)
.SH NOTES
.PP
Man pages follow the same convention as all Zensical documentation skills.
Each skill stores its man page at
.IR <skill-path>/man/<skill-name>.1 .
Use
.BR man (1)
with the skill name to view a skill's documentation.
